\par 
\par {\b Why Use It...}{\b 
\par }Although most end users will likely find this Leash feature irrelevant, application developers and support staff may occasionally find it to be useful. For example, you may want an immediate status check of Kerberos tickets if you have just used {\uldb 
kinit}{\v ID_HELP_KINIT} or {\uldb kdestroy }{\v ID_HELP_KDESTROY} and want to check that they have functioned successfully.
\par 
\par {\b How It Works...}
\par While Leash automatically checks the status of your Kerberos tickets every 30 seconds, the Update Display command forces an immediate status check.
